				\begin{document}$$-2$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M4"><mml:mrow><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2022_4789_Article_IEq2.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> position. However, compared with <italic>D. melanogaster</italic> and <italic>A. thaliana</italic>, A and T were significantly enriched only at a few positions in <italic>E. coli</italic>. In <italic>G. subterraneus</italic> and <italic>G. pickeringii</italic>, C and G were significantly over-represented at upstream (<inline-formula id="IEq3"><alternatives><tex-math id="M5">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
