      </sec>
    </sec>
    <sec id="Sec18">
      <title>Model training setup</title>
      <p id="Par62">Hyb4mC was implemented in Python 3.6 using Keras (2.1.6) with the backend of TensorFlow (1.12.0). In the Hyb_Caps subnet, a margin loss function was used, defined in Eq. <xref rid="Equ5" ref-type="">5</xref>. The training process used 10-fold cross-validation. The number of epochs was set to 30, and the batch size was set to 16. Meanwhile, we performed 10-fold cross-validation on the training dataset. In the Hyb_Conv subnet, the binary cross entropy was set as the loss function, defined in Eq. <xref rid="Equ6" ref-type="">6</xref>. The epoch was set to 90, and the batch size was set to 64. The Adam optimizer was used in both subnetworks.<disp-formula id="Equ5"><label>5</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M31">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
